WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.636 --> 00:00:15.181
[Japanese rock theme music playing]

2
00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:23.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

3
00:01:27.420 --> 00:01:30.715
[in English] ♪ <i>Don't be. be. be afraid </i>♪

4
00:01:31.424 --> 00:01:35.512
<i>♪ Don't be. be. be. be. be afraid ♪</i>

5
00:01:35.595 --> 00:01:41.017
BAKI-DOU: THE INVINCIBLE SAMURAI

6
00:01:45.605 --> 00:01:50.026
{\an8}CRIMINAL INVESTIGATION. VIOLENT CRIME
KO SUEMITSU. CHIEF EIICHIRO HIKIGI

7
00:01:53.113 --> 00:01:56.908
[man 1] Loose long hair.
traditional garb. and barefoot.

8
00:01:58.243 --> 00:02:01.579
He's a perfect match to that description
they gave us back at the station.

9
00:02:01.663 --> 00:02:05.041
- He hasn't changed his appearance.
- It's like he wants to be seen.

10
00:02:05.792 --> 00:02:08.336
[Ko] Well. he is the greatest samurai
that ever lived.

11
00:02:08.419 --> 00:02:10.588
- [Eiichiro] Hmm.
- [both chuckle]

12
00:02:16.636 --> 00:02:17.887
He stopped.

13
00:02:17.971 --> 00:02:20.181
Keep walking. Just act casual.

14
00:02:22.767 --> 00:02:23.685
[both gasp]

15
00:02:29.107 --> 00:02:30.316
What do we do now?

16
00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:33.069
We can't exactly turn around. can we?

17
00:02:38.908 --> 00:02:40.034
[both gasp]

18
00:02:40.910 --> 00:02:42.829
[both breathing heavily]

19
00:02:43.913 --> 00:02:45.832
[Ko] Hikigi. hold on a second isn't this--

20
00:02:45.915 --> 00:02:47.792
The Tokugawa residence!

21
00:02:47.876 --> 00:02:49.961
We better report this
back to headquarters.

22
00:02:50.044 --> 00:02:51.629
This can't be good.

23
00:02:51.713 --> 00:02:52.714
[Ko] I'm on it!

24
00:02:52.797 --> 00:02:54.591
[dramatic music sting]

25
00:02:58.803 --> 00:03:00.972
Somebody saw a trespasser?

26
00:03:01.055 --> 00:03:01.931
{\an8}Apparently. so.

27
00:03:02.015 --> 00:03:03.099
{\an8}POLICE CHIEF
TESTU MISHIRO

28
00:03:03.183 --> 00:03:05.351
{\an8}Some of my agents saw
a man enter the compound.

29
00:03:05.435 --> 00:03:08.062
I'm not bothered.
so you can forget all about it.

30
00:03:08.146 --> 00:03:10.648
Yes. sir.
But it's important you understand.

31
00:03:10.732 --> 00:03:14.110
The individual is currently a suspect
in an ongoing operation.

32
00:03:14.194 --> 00:03:16.696
Mr. Musashi? He's your suspect?

33
00:03:16.779 --> 00:03:18.239
Well. I mean…

34
00:03:18.323 --> 00:03:21.492
Yes. he's considered
to be quite dangerous.

35
00:03:21.576 --> 00:03:24.495
Mr. Mishiro. tell Utsumi the following.

36
00:03:24.579 --> 00:03:27.874
Utsu… You mean… Shunzo Utsumi?

37
00:03:28.374 --> 00:03:30.501
The Superintendent-General himself?

38
00:03:30.585 --> 00:03:31.878
Just leave him be.

39
00:03:31.961 --> 00:03:34.547
You can observe him. but do not intervene.

40
00:03:34.631 --> 00:03:36.507
Tell him Tokugawa said so.

41
00:03:36.591 --> 00:03:37.675
[gasps]

42
00:03:38.593 --> 00:03:41.137
Got it. Mr. Mishiro?

43
00:03:41.221 --> 00:03:44.641
Certainly. sir!
I will make sure to pass on your message.

44
00:03:44.724 --> 00:03:46.351
[gate squeaking]

45
00:03:49.229 --> 00:03:50.480
[groans softly]

46
00:03:50.563 --> 00:03:52.649
Now then. shall we continue?

47
00:03:55.568 --> 00:03:57.237
[intriguing music playing]

48
00:03:59.530 --> 00:04:03.618
[Tokugawa] What brought you here?
What are you hoping to find out?

49
00:04:05.203 --> 00:04:06.871
Look. Mitsunari.

50
00:04:06.955 --> 00:04:08.289
You happen to be the owner

51
00:04:08.373 --> 00:04:10.917
of the underground arena
beneath Tokyo Dome.

52
00:04:11.417 --> 00:04:12.919
So I know you hear things.

53
00:04:13.002 --> 00:04:16.881
You get all the latest intel
on the strongest men in Japan and beyond.

54
00:04:16.965 --> 00:04:20.093
When it comes to people
with the potential for great strengths.

55
00:04:20.176 --> 00:04:24.138
I don't think there's a single man
in Japan you're not keeping tabs on.

56
00:04:24.222 --> 00:04:25.139
[Tokugawa] Hmm.

57
00:04:26.432 --> 00:04:27.642
[slurping]

58
00:04:30.561 --> 00:04:32.897
I know he doesn't use karate or judo.

59
00:04:32.981 --> 00:04:35.483
He fights differently
than anything I've ever seen.

60
00:04:35.566 --> 00:04:38.027
Well. then. What technique does he use?

61
00:04:38.111 --> 00:04:42.031
He claims to be someone famous.
Musashi Miyamoto.

62
00:04:42.782 --> 00:04:44.033
A samurai.

63
00:04:44.117 --> 00:04:45.118
[gasps softly]

64
00:04:45.618 --> 00:04:48.288
But either way.
he's on a whole 'nother level.

65
00:04:48.871 --> 00:04:50.832
<i>His ability to draw his blade to attack</i>

66
00:04:50.915 --> 00:04:53.793
<i>is at least twice as fast</i>
<i>as a typical swordsman.</i>

67
00:04:53.876 --> 00:04:56.296
Wait. wait. wait. wait.

68
00:04:56.379 --> 00:04:58.298
Doppo. seriously?

69
00:04:58.381 --> 00:05:01.009
You're telling me
you think he's the real thing?

70
00:05:01.092 --> 00:05:04.554
It doesn't matter to me whether
he's the genuine article or a fake.

71
00:05:05.263 --> 00:05:09.559
{\an8}His skills appear real enough to my eyes.
That's all I care about.

72
00:05:11.644 --> 00:05:14.147
It's putting you on edge. isn't it. Doppo?

73
00:05:15.606 --> 00:05:17.150
I wanna meet him.

74
00:05:17.650 --> 00:05:19.068
Doppo.

75
00:05:21.154 --> 00:05:22.905
- [Doppo] Huh?
- [Tokugawa gasps]

76
00:05:24.157 --> 00:05:27.118
Hey! I'm hungry!

77
00:05:28.661 --> 00:05:31.539
Oh. You have a guest. pardon me.

78
00:05:31.622 --> 00:05:32.582
Not at all.

79
00:05:32.665 --> 00:05:34.167
Mr. Musashi.

80
00:05:35.168 --> 00:05:37.086
I know this is a sudden request.

81
00:05:37.170 --> 00:05:40.423
but what do you make
of the man seated here?

82
00:05:42.925 --> 00:05:45.428
Well… for a man like him.

83
00:05:45.511 --> 00:05:47.889
I think I could finish him off
before the meal.

84
00:05:48.681 --> 00:05:50.183
[nervous grumbling]

85
00:05:50.683 --> 00:05:53.644
[Tokugawa] Are you suggesting
the God of Martial Arts. Doppo Orochi.

86
00:05:53.728 --> 00:05:54.729
is an appetizer?

87
00:06:01.736 --> 00:06:03.988
That appears to be the case. Doppo.

88
00:06:04.072 --> 00:06:05.198
[chuckling]

89
00:06:05.281 --> 00:06:06.991
I must apologize.

90
00:06:07.075 --> 00:06:08.326
[grumbles nervously]

91
00:06:12.080 --> 00:06:15.583
The conditions don't matter to me.
But I would like to spar.

92
00:06:15.666 --> 00:06:18.002
Even just once would do. Hell. I…

93
00:06:18.086 --> 00:06:21.297
I think I would've been satisfied
just meeting you.

94
00:06:21.381 --> 00:06:23.007
You're a legend. you know.

95
00:06:23.091 --> 00:06:27.053
And now you're sitting there.
History's greatest samurai in this room.

96
00:06:27.136 --> 00:06:30.014
Even better. he says he's willing
to engage me in a fight.

97
00:06:30.973 --> 00:06:33.893
Frankly. this all seems
a little too good to be true.

98
00:06:35.103 --> 00:06:39.023
Did you hear what he said. Musashi?
It feels too good to be true.

99
00:06:42.360 --> 00:06:43.778
I'm being restrained.

100
00:06:44.445 --> 00:06:45.530
[Tokugawa] Hmm?

101
00:06:45.613 --> 00:06:47.532
[tense music sting]

102
00:06:47.615 --> 00:06:50.868
From the moment I entered this room
to when I sat down here.

103
00:06:50.952 --> 00:06:52.412
three times I tried.

104
00:06:52.495 --> 00:06:53.538
[Tokugawa] Huh?

105
00:06:53.621 --> 00:06:57.417
But each time I went to draw my sword.
my head was held down.

106
00:06:57.500 --> 00:06:58.668
[Tokugawa chuckles]

107
00:06:58.751 --> 00:07:00.294
I think we should wait.

108
00:07:00.378 --> 00:07:02.922
Wouldn't it be better
if you had something to eat?

109
00:07:03.005 --> 00:07:05.049
Not at all! I'd rather fight first.

110
00:07:05.133 --> 00:07:06.551
[Tokugawa] Oh…

111
00:07:12.140 --> 00:07:14.350
[Tokugawa] This dojo is used
by our servants

112
00:07:14.434 --> 00:07:16.561
for martial arts and dance practice.

113
00:07:16.644 --> 00:07:17.770
[Musashi] Hmm.

114
00:07:18.646 --> 00:07:20.148
This should suffice.

115
00:07:20.231 --> 00:07:21.941
By the way. Mr. Miyamoto.

116
00:07:22.024 --> 00:07:24.610
I know the two of you
are raring to get started.

117
00:07:24.694 --> 00:07:29.323
but I would like to allow Doppo Orochi
to introduce himself his way.

118
00:07:29.407 --> 00:07:30.366
[gasps]

119
00:07:31.409 --> 00:07:33.077
- Kanou.
- Sir.

120
00:07:33.161 --> 00:07:35.079
[suspenseful music playing]

121
00:07:35.663 --> 00:07:37.081
[Doppo chuckles]

122
00:07:37.165 --> 00:07:41.669
Seeing is believing. so this'll be faster
than trying to explain it.

123
00:07:41.752 --> 00:07:44.088
I'd like to see it too. It's been a while.

124
00:07:44.172 --> 00:07:45.339
[Musashi] Hmm?

125
00:07:46.174 --> 00:07:47.300
[Doppo] Well. why not?

126
00:07:47.383 --> 00:07:50.094
I never miss an opportunity
to show off my skills.

127
00:07:53.055 --> 00:07:54.765
[suspenseful music playing]

128
00:07:57.477 --> 00:07:58.686
[Doppo grunts]

129
00:08:09.697 --> 00:08:11.115
[chuckling]

130
00:08:11.199 --> 00:08:12.700
- [Doppo grunts]
- [glass smashes]

131
00:08:15.286 --> 00:08:16.621
[Doppo grunts]

132
00:08:18.873 --> 00:08:19.874
[bones crunching]

133
00:08:22.168 --> 00:08:23.878
[Doppo grunts]

134
00:08:25.046 --> 00:08:25.880
Huh.

135
00:08:29.842 --> 00:08:31.761
[Doppo] Yah!

136
00:08:36.849 --> 00:08:38.851
The name's Doppo Orochi.

137
00:08:39.352 --> 00:08:41.771
[Tokugawa] <i>Eh.</i>
<i>how will Musashi react to that?</i>

138
00:08:41.854 --> 00:08:43.105
[Musashi] Well.

139
00:08:44.732 --> 00:08:48.277
I'd say it's less martial arts
and more of a dance.

140
00:08:48.361 --> 00:08:51.489
But why wood and stones?
What's the point of that?

141
00:08:51.572 --> 00:08:52.782
[Doppo seethes]

142
00:08:52.865 --> 00:08:55.868
Hold on. Seriously?

143
00:08:57.870 --> 00:08:59.789
[Tokugawa] <i>It's… it's happening.</i>

144
00:08:59.872 --> 00:09:01.791
A dance?

145
00:09:01.874 --> 00:09:04.293
Did I upset you. Mr. Orochi?

146
00:09:04.377 --> 00:09:06.170
[Doppo] Damn right. you did.

147
00:09:07.004 --> 00:09:09.924
[Tokugawa] <i>Am I really gonna see</i>
<i>Doppo Orochi fight?!</i>

148
00:09:10.007 --> 00:09:13.177
Could be a dance. but it could be
something more than that too.

149
00:09:13.844 --> 00:09:17.014
How about we put that to the test
right here. right now?

150
00:09:17.515 --> 00:09:20.476
[Tokugawa] <i>This isn't about sparring.</i>
<i>nor a contest of strength.</i>

151
00:09:20.560 --> 00:09:22.019
<i>It's an actual fight!</i>

152
00:09:22.520 --> 00:09:23.563
Huh?

153
00:09:27.441 --> 00:09:29.193
[roaring]

154
00:09:29.277 --> 00:09:30.194
[Tokugawa gasps]

155
00:09:32.280 --> 00:09:34.198
[dramatic music sting]

156
00:09:34.782 --> 00:09:37.201
Forgive me. Mr. Orochi.

157
00:09:37.285 --> 00:09:39.453
I wanted to tease you a little.

158
00:09:39.537 --> 00:09:40.955
[Doppo growls softly]

159
00:09:43.040 --> 00:09:44.959
[Tokugawa] <i>His skills</i>…

160
00:09:45.042 --> 00:09:49.213
That demonstration earlier.
The one with your bare hands.

161
00:09:49.297 --> 00:09:52.216
I must admit
that I knew it was martial arts.

162
00:09:52.300 --> 00:09:54.218
[Tokugawa] <i>You're on</i>
<i>a whole different level.</i>

163
00:09:56.304 --> 00:09:58.222
I was able to see it all.

164
00:09:58.931 --> 00:10:02.226
<i>The actions were yours alone.</i>
<i>but I could see their intended opponent.</i>

165
00:10:02.810 --> 00:10:06.731
<i>They may not have been formidable enemies.</i>
<i>but they were by no means easy targets.</i>

166
00:10:07.565 --> 00:10:11.444
<i>Striking sharp and heavy.</i>
<i>you defeated five people at once.</i>

167
00:10:11.527 --> 00:10:14.363
It was a splendid sight to see.
Master Orochi.

168
00:10:14.447 --> 00:10:16.866
Ah. enough with the flattery.

169
00:10:16.949 --> 00:10:20.369
The fact you dodged my surprise headbutt
is embarrassing enough.

170
00:10:20.453 --> 00:10:22.747
Don't add insult to injury
with a compliment.

171
00:10:22.830 --> 00:10:23.831
What?

172
00:10:24.665 --> 00:10:26.250
You rubbed my bald head.

173
00:10:27.168 --> 00:10:30.254
You're out of your damn mind
if you think I'll let that slide.

174
00:10:30.838 --> 00:10:32.006
Go on. then.

175
00:10:32.089 --> 00:10:33.758
[groaning nervously]

176
00:10:33.841 --> 00:10:35.509
[tense music playing]

177
00:10:43.392 --> 00:10:44.435
[Musashi] Ready?

178
00:10:48.356 --> 00:10:49.774
[Doppo] <i>It's just as I thought.</i>

179
00:10:49.857 --> 00:10:52.526
I knew you'd have your swords.

180
00:10:57.865 --> 00:10:59.116
[Doppo groans painfully]

181
00:10:59.867 --> 00:11:02.995
<i>He's standing back.</i>
<i>He's not holding anything.</i>

182
00:11:03.079 --> 00:11:03.996
<i>But somehow.</i>

183
00:11:04.080 --> 00:11:07.792
<i>I feel like I'm being threatened</i>
<i>by the point of a sword I can't see.</i>

184
00:11:09.877 --> 00:11:11.796
[dramatic music playing]

185
00:11:11.879 --> 00:11:13.297
[grunts ferociously]

186
00:11:17.885 --> 00:11:18.886
<i>Huh</i>.

187
00:11:23.391 --> 00:11:25.518
[pained yelling]

188
00:11:25.601 --> 00:11:27.561
- [Musashi laughs]
- Huh?

189
00:11:27.645 --> 00:11:29.313
See. I told you.

190
00:11:29.397 --> 00:11:31.816
It really was just a dance. Orochi.

191
00:11:31.899 --> 00:11:33.317
[Doppo groans]

192
00:11:33.401 --> 00:11:34.819
[Doppo yelps]

193
00:11:34.902 --> 00:11:36.904
[Musashi] I don't even need to cut you.

194
00:11:38.406 --> 00:11:39.824
[Doppo grunts]

195
00:11:48.249 --> 00:11:49.333
[Doppo grunts]

196
00:11:49.959 --> 00:11:51.335
[growling]

197
00:11:52.712 --> 00:11:53.838
[Tokugawa] <i>Whoa.</i>

198
00:11:53.921 --> 00:11:55.923
<i>The Tenchi-Jouge Stance.</i>

199
00:11:56.006 --> 00:11:59.218
<i>He's not giving up!</i>
<i>Doppo's still got plenty of fight in him!</i>

200
00:11:59.301 --> 00:12:02.346
Why do you still stand?
How is that possible?

201
00:12:03.180 --> 00:12:04.348
[Doppo] Ah.

202
00:12:04.432 --> 00:12:08.602
I stood up 'cause I can still stand.
What are you confused about?

203
00:12:09.228 --> 00:12:12.606
But I did cut you. I thought you noticed.

204
00:12:12.690 --> 00:12:14.108
[Tokugawa] Huh?

205
00:12:14.191 --> 00:12:15.401
Right here.

206
00:12:15.484 --> 00:12:18.612
A single stroke across the body.
Diagonally. like this.

207
00:12:18.696 --> 00:12:20.740
So then you understand my technique?

208
00:12:21.365 --> 00:12:23.367
Of course. You mimicked cutting me.

209
00:12:23.451 --> 00:12:25.327
You call that mimicry?

210
00:12:25.411 --> 00:12:27.955
[Doppo] Musashi Miyamoto.
your biggest mistake was

211
00:12:28.038 --> 00:12:31.375
that you chose to stand before me
without your real swords.

212
00:12:31.459 --> 00:12:32.334
Ah.

213
00:12:32.835 --> 00:12:37.006
But it wasn't a feint. And yet.
I can clearly see that you weren't cut.

214
00:12:38.966 --> 00:12:40.468
Understood!

215
00:12:40.968 --> 00:12:42.720
- Sir Tokugawa.
- [Tokugawa] Hmm?

216
00:12:42.803 --> 00:12:44.138
Do you own any swords?

217
00:12:45.181 --> 00:12:48.642
A Tokugawa is a Tokugawa.
no matter how shriveled I end up.

218
00:12:49.685 --> 00:12:51.771
The national treasure. Kunitora.

219
00:12:51.854 --> 00:12:53.522
our most prized heirloom.

220
00:12:53.606 --> 00:12:55.191
But I'll lend it to ya.

221
00:12:57.735 --> 00:12:59.195
[metal glistening]

222
00:13:05.868 --> 00:13:07.661
Ah. A very good sword.

223
00:13:08.454 --> 00:13:09.914
This one will hold.

224
00:13:13.501 --> 00:13:16.170
Apologies for the wait. Master Orochi.

225
00:13:16.253 --> 00:13:18.172
Don't worry about it at all.

226
00:13:18.255 --> 00:13:21.133
I'm the one who provoked you
to use a real sword.

227
00:13:21.217 --> 00:13:22.551
Doppo.

228
00:13:22.635 --> 00:13:24.678
I'll explain the details later.

229
00:13:24.762 --> 00:13:28.724
I know you think he's only pretending
to be Musashi. but you're wrong!

230
00:13:28.808 --> 00:13:31.060
He's the real Musashi Miyamoto!

231
00:13:31.143 --> 00:13:32.311
So what?

232
00:13:32.394 --> 00:13:35.147
You know I don't care
for lengthy explanations.

233
00:13:35.231 --> 00:13:38.108
I don't give a damn
about how he came to be here.

234
00:13:38.192 --> 00:13:40.069
I can tell he's the real deal.

235
00:13:40.152 --> 00:13:43.239
That's exactly why
I wanted him to have a sword.

236
00:13:43.989 --> 00:13:46.158
This is no laughing matter. Doppo!

237
00:13:46.242 --> 00:13:49.078
You're giving a living legend
his weapon of choice!

238
00:13:49.161 --> 00:13:50.830
What are you doing. Doppo? He's--

239
00:13:50.913 --> 00:13:53.457
What I'm doing
is making sure he's armed too.

240
00:13:55.543 --> 00:13:57.962
Because karate turns
your whole body into a weapon.

241
00:13:58.546 --> 00:14:01.966
Hand sword. foot blade.
spear hand. and front kick.

242
00:14:02.049 --> 00:14:05.219
I've got plenty of weapons
in my arsenal to choose from.

243
00:14:06.095 --> 00:14:07.054
[Musashi chuckles]

244
00:14:07.805 --> 00:14:09.223
[Tokugawa groans nervously]

245
00:14:10.808 --> 00:14:13.435
I find the things you say funny..

246
00:14:13.519 --> 00:14:15.437
Both of you are rather amusing

247
00:14:15.521 --> 00:14:16.730
[laughing heartily]

248
00:14:16.814 --> 00:14:18.232
What?!

249
00:14:19.817 --> 00:14:22.611
You dare call a mortal
the God of Martial Arts.

250
00:14:22.695 --> 00:14:25.072
and the mortal willingly accepts the name.

251
00:14:25.155 --> 00:14:29.118
Your fragile body can't cut paper.
but you talk of spears and blades?

252
00:14:29.201 --> 00:14:31.370
Maybe it's less than a dance.

253
00:14:31.453 --> 00:14:32.371
[Tokugawa gasps]

254
00:14:32.454 --> 00:14:34.623
- [tense music continues]
- [Doppo growling]

255
00:14:43.591 --> 00:14:45.509
[thunderous boom echoes]

256
00:14:47.970 --> 00:14:49.263
[Tokugawa gasps]

257
00:14:50.180 --> 00:14:51.348
You cut…

258
00:14:56.353 --> 00:14:57.271
No.

259
00:14:58.063 --> 00:14:59.273
I didn't cut him.

260
00:15:00.524 --> 00:15:01.775
I touched him

261
00:15:02.359 --> 00:15:03.569
and pressed.

262
00:15:06.614 --> 00:15:10.284
Just that bit of pressure?
That's not enough to cut through anyone.

263
00:15:10.367 --> 00:15:11.785
[Tokugawa] <i>Wow.</i>

264
00:15:14.663 --> 00:15:16.165
Here. I'll show you.

265
00:15:18.375 --> 00:15:20.586
You have to pull when applying pressure.

266
00:15:22.963 --> 00:15:27.051
That's how a blade functions.
And that's how skin functions too.

267
00:15:27.134 --> 00:15:30.095
Even the treasured heirloom sword.
Kunitora.

268
00:15:30.179 --> 00:15:32.932
is bound by that unyielding principle.

269
00:15:36.018 --> 00:15:37.019
[Musashi] Hmm?

270
00:15:37.937 --> 00:15:40.439
Oh-ho. Well. isn't this interesting?

271
00:15:41.190 --> 00:15:43.817
I must reflect on this fight more deeply.

272
00:15:44.485 --> 00:15:48.572
A fragile body that can't cut paper?
I was mistaken.

273
00:15:48.656 --> 00:15:49.949
Orochi.

274
00:15:50.032 --> 00:15:52.868
Your hands and feet
are fine blades indeed!

275
00:15:53.577 --> 00:15:55.537
[narrator] <i>The defeated</i>
<i>was lying at his feet.</i>

276
00:15:55.621 --> 00:15:58.332
<i>and the victors praise</i>
<i>fell shamelessly from his lips.</i>

277
00:15:59.083 --> 00:16:02.336
<i>All the praise aside.</i>
<i>the truth was. he could not move.</i>

278
00:16:03.128 --> 00:16:04.964
<i>He had been cut down!</i>

279
00:16:10.219 --> 00:16:11.303
A clone?

280
00:16:12.179 --> 00:16:14.640
[Tokugawa] I know
the explanation is confusing.

281
00:16:14.723 --> 00:16:18.102
but all that actually happened
to bring Musashi back to life.

282
00:16:20.187 --> 00:16:21.772
Convinced yet?

283
00:16:22.439 --> 00:16:24.149
Try to convince me all you want.

284
00:16:24.233 --> 00:16:26.735
I don't understand
a damn thing you're saying.

285
00:16:27.361 --> 00:16:28.362
All the same.

286
00:16:28.445 --> 00:16:30.864
what I do understand
is what my body tells me.

287
00:16:30.948 --> 00:16:34.618
{\an8}And what it's telling me is
that was the real Musashi Miyamoto.

288
00:16:36.495 --> 00:16:38.580
Good instincts. [clears throat]

289
00:16:38.664 --> 00:16:40.708
This is never an easy thing to ask.

290
00:16:40.791 --> 00:16:43.627
but. uh. about the fight
and how it turned out.

291
00:16:43.711 --> 00:16:46.296
I just lost a fight. I lost the match.

292
00:16:46.380 --> 00:16:48.132
I've been bested. thoroughly.

293
00:16:48.215 --> 00:16:51.135
It's been so long.
losing a fight almost feels refreshing.

294
00:16:52.011 --> 00:16:55.389
<i>The Japanese katana is a blade</i>
<i>unparalleled in its sharpness.</i>

295
00:16:55.472 --> 00:16:57.850
{\an8}A single stroke can split you in half.

296
00:16:57.933 --> 00:17:00.394
{\an8}which might have been
a better fate for me.

297
00:17:01.061 --> 00:17:03.939
<i>He struck. pressed in. but did not cut.</i>

298
00:17:04.023 --> 00:17:08.027
<i>He won without inflicting a single wound.</i>
<i>A mercy that is hard to bear.</i>

299
00:17:08.110 --> 00:17:10.946
Tokugawa. today I suffered
something far more humbling

300
00:17:11.030 --> 00:17:12.614
than just a simple defeat.

301
00:17:13.115 --> 00:17:17.536
{\an8}If a warrior opponent shows you mercy.
the battle is already over.

302
00:17:18.162 --> 00:17:20.873
A wound far worse than a sword slash.

303
00:17:21.373 --> 00:17:24.918
I don't know what to tell you.
I'm speechless.

304
00:17:25.002 --> 00:17:27.546
I'm grateful though. I mean it.

305
00:17:27.629 --> 00:17:28.839
[Tokugawa] Hmm.

306
00:17:30.799 --> 00:17:33.677
[Doppo] The Book of Five Rings
<i>is always on my bookshelf.</i>

307
00:17:35.763 --> 00:17:38.932
<i>I've lost count</i>
<i>of how many times I've read it.</i>

308
00:17:39.767 --> 00:17:41.268
I know it by heart.

309
00:17:42.811 --> 00:17:45.564
<i>And yet. I realized a hard truth</i>
<i>in that moment.</i>

310
00:17:45.647 --> 00:17:47.274
<i>Despite the number of times I've read it.</i>

311
00:17:47.357 --> 00:17:49.568
<i>I never even came close</i>
<i>to understanding it.</i>

312
00:17:50.360 --> 00:17:54.073
Oh. that does make sense.
He's the one who wrote it. after all.

313
00:17:54.156 --> 00:17:56.450
With all my experience. he put me down.

314
00:17:56.533 --> 00:17:58.702
Effectively told me I wasn't worth a damn.

315
00:17:58.786 --> 00:18:02.206
[Tokugawa] Will you continue?
Or will you withdraw?

316
00:18:04.124 --> 00:18:04.958
[slurping]

317
00:18:06.043 --> 00:18:09.088
[Doppo] <i>I'm gonna shut myself out</i>
<i>from the world for a bit.</i>

318
00:18:10.422 --> 00:18:11.965
[narrator] <i>Narita Airport.</i>

319
00:18:12.466 --> 00:18:15.219
[camera shutters clicking]

320
00:18:15.302 --> 00:18:16.970
[camera shutters clicking]

321
00:18:17.971 --> 00:18:20.724
[man 1] We were told your match
was just an exhibition.

322
00:18:21.350 --> 00:18:24.978
How does it differ from an official match?
Would you like to comment?

323
00:18:25.062 --> 00:18:28.065
[Retsu] It was different
because I did not use my legs.

324
00:18:28.565 --> 00:18:29.983
Or my knees.

325
00:18:30.692 --> 00:18:31.985
Or my elbows.

326
00:18:32.069 --> 00:18:33.695
[camera shutters clicking]

327
00:18:33.779 --> 00:18:35.489
Only fists.

328
00:18:37.324 --> 00:18:41.745
<i>I targeted Mr. Bolt's upper body.</i>
<i>And all my attacks were from the front.</i>

329
00:18:41.829 --> 00:18:42.788
[crowd cheering]

330
00:18:42.871 --> 00:18:44.998
[Retsu] <i>And with those restrictions.</i>
<i>I won.</i>

331
00:18:45.833 --> 00:18:47.584
In the end. I was the victor.

332
00:18:48.127 --> 00:18:50.504
I believe that's all there is to it.

333
00:18:50.587 --> 00:18:54.258
It doesn't matter
whether it was an official fight or not.

334
00:18:55.134 --> 00:18:58.762
<i>It doesn't matter whether I got that belt</i>
<i>from Mr. Kaiser or not.</i>

335
00:18:59.388 --> 00:19:01.640
{\an8}It doesn't matter if it gets recognized.

336
00:19:02.432 --> 00:19:04.893
{\an8}That's outside my scope of knowledge.

337
00:19:04.977 --> 00:19:06.395
{\an8}Nor do I care.

338
00:19:06.478 --> 00:19:08.147
[reporters gasping]

339
00:19:08.730 --> 00:19:10.732
Chinese kung fu is my focus.

340
00:19:11.233 --> 00:19:13.527
But I was only allowed to use part of it.

341
00:19:14.153 --> 00:19:16.029
And even so. I managed to win!

342
00:19:16.864 --> 00:19:18.031
That's all!

343
00:19:18.115 --> 00:19:19.575
[reporters mumbling in shock]

344
00:19:19.658 --> 00:19:22.035
- [man 2] Oh. Mr. Retsu!
- [man 3] Retsu. wait!

345
00:19:23.245 --> 00:19:25.789
[man 4] What are you planning
on doing in Japan?

346
00:19:25.873 --> 00:19:28.000
I won't be defending my title.

347
00:19:28.500 --> 00:19:29.918
I'm done with boxing.

348
00:19:30.544 --> 00:19:32.963
I'm not officially a boxer after all.

349
00:19:33.505 --> 00:19:35.716
What will you be doing while you're here?

350
00:19:35.799 --> 00:19:38.010
Are you not going to fight anymore?

351
00:19:40.512 --> 00:19:43.015
I don't want to use parts of it.
I want it all.

352
00:19:43.098 --> 00:19:44.057
Uh. sorry?

353
00:19:44.725 --> 00:19:45.767
[Retsu] <i>Fists.</i>

354
00:19:47.060 --> 00:19:49.313
Tai. <i>or kicks.</i>

355
00:19:50.105 --> 00:19:51.440
<i>Piercing hand.</i>

356
00:19:51.523 --> 00:19:55.944
<i>Sword. Spear. Staff. Even </i>shuriken.

357
00:19:57.404 --> 00:20:01.575
An opponent has appeared in Japan.
Against him. I can use them all.

358
00:20:01.658 --> 00:20:04.578
KARATE-DO
SHINSHINKAI HEADQUARTERS

359
00:20:04.661 --> 00:20:05.662
Huh?!

360
00:20:06.663 --> 00:20:08.415
He was defeated?!

361
00:20:08.916 --> 00:20:10.334
Orochi lost?!

362
00:20:10.417 --> 00:20:11.752
[gasps uneasily]

363
00:20:12.377 --> 00:20:14.004
I'm afraid it's worse than that.

364
00:20:14.087 --> 00:20:15.339
To put it simply.

365
00:20:16.298 --> 00:20:17.674
{\an8}he was thrashed.

366
00:20:18.175 --> 00:20:19.218
[Retsu] Hmm.

367
00:20:19.301 --> 00:20:22.471
Doppo Orochi. He's a skilled man.

368
00:20:22.554 --> 00:20:26.016
In karate and other martial arts.
he's one of the best.

369
00:20:26.099 --> 00:20:27.351
Very strong.

370
00:20:28.936 --> 00:20:31.396
Perhaps the best at karate in the world.

371
00:20:31.939 --> 00:20:36.360
But in spite of that. he still lost.
and a truly decisive loss at that.

372
00:20:37.069 --> 00:20:39.112
The result. you don't mind?

373
00:20:41.657 --> 00:20:43.575
The battle was fought fair and square.

374
00:20:43.659 --> 00:20:46.119
There were no dirty tricks
or forbidden techniques

375
00:20:46.203 --> 00:20:48.872
That's why. even if I were to fight him.

376
00:20:49.373 --> 00:20:51.625
if I tried taking on Musashi Miyamoto.

377
00:20:52.584 --> 00:20:54.169
{\an8}it wouldn't be for revenge.

378
00:20:54.253 --> 00:20:56.380
{\an8}but rather for me to prove it to myself.

379
00:20:56.463 --> 00:20:57.464
[Retsu] Hmm.

380
00:20:58.465 --> 00:20:59.883
He uses weapons. you know.

381
00:21:02.302 --> 00:21:05.389
I didn't expect to hear that
from someone like you. Retsu.

382
00:21:05.472 --> 00:21:06.390
Huh?!

383
00:21:06.974 --> 00:21:10.185
Both techniques.
karate and kung fu. should be adequate.

384
00:21:10.269 --> 00:21:13.647
They're both martial arts designed
to overcome any situation.

385
00:21:13.730 --> 00:21:16.358
Against weapons. multiple opponents…

386
00:21:16.441 --> 00:21:19.152
No matter the circumstances.
the technique is always there.

387
00:21:19.236 --> 00:21:20.404
ready at your command.

388
00:21:20.487 --> 00:21:22.531
Isn't that the nature of the form?

389
00:21:23.031 --> 00:21:25.909
That's what karate
and kung fu are all about.

390
00:21:29.246 --> 00:21:31.665
I watched a video of him on a website.

391
00:21:32.958 --> 00:21:37.504
<i>He was surrounded by five police officers.</i>
<i>He took them on all by himself.</i>

392
00:21:38.630 --> 00:21:40.549
One after another.

393
00:21:41.383 --> 00:21:43.760
<i>He took each one down like it was nothing.</i>

394
00:21:46.221 --> 00:21:48.140
<i>They never stood a chance.</i>

395
00:21:49.808 --> 00:21:51.393
<i>Even if there were more</i>…

396
00:21:51.476 --> 00:21:52.811
<i>There could have been 20.</i>

397
00:21:53.603 --> 00:21:55.355
<i>it would've been just the same.</i>

398
00:21:56.523 --> 00:21:58.608
You saw that too. Retsu.

399
00:21:58.692 --> 00:22:00.193
I don't want to admit it.

400
00:22:00.777 --> 00:22:03.196
but while our techniques
defend against weapons.

401
00:22:03.280 --> 00:22:05.991
they were never meant to be tested
against that level.

402
00:22:06.074 --> 00:22:07.576
Someone like yourself.

403
00:22:07.659 --> 00:22:09.786
I'm sure you knew that already.

404
00:22:12.331 --> 00:22:14.082
- Katsumi.
- Mm?

405
00:22:14.666 --> 00:22:16.835
Don't hesitate to use your weapon!

406
00:22:17.336 --> 00:22:20.130
Don't think twice about it
when going against him!

407
00:22:21.840 --> 00:22:25.427
- ["Mountain Top" by Novel Core playing]
- [lyrics in Japanese]

408
00:23:34.204 --> 00:23:35.372
{\an8}[in English] ♪ <i>Yeah </i>♪

409
00:23:35.455 --> 00:23:38.041
{\an8}<i>♪ Yeah. yeah ♪</i>

410
00:23:38.583 --> 00:23:40.710
{\an8}<i>♪ I'm on the mountaintop. yeah </i>♪

411
00:23:41.586 --> 00:23:44.172
{\an8}<i>♪ Yeah. yeah ♪</i>

412
00:23:44.673 --> 00:23:46.758
{\an8}<i>♪ I'm on the mountaintop. yeah </i>♪

413
00:23:49.261 --> 00:23:50.429
{\an8}[music fades out]

414
00:23:51.305 --> 00:24:51.356
